The old LowDiskPauseProcessor implementation is a mess -- dependent on 
&#39;df&#39; output that varies, and using Runtime.exec() (which even for the 
smallest program needs address space equal to the JVM process to fork).

It should be updated to use the new official java free-space checks. In 
H3, also, it need not be a Processor -- it could be more like 
CrawlLimitEnforcer, a singleton bean receiving crawl events. It also 
might not need explicit configuration of paths to monitor -- requesting 
a list of all ConfigPaths, as the job resource page does, should be 
enough for it to know all volumes on which the crawl is relying.

So yes, your alternative would be a welcome addition to H3, and we&#39;ll 
deprecate or just remove LowDiskPauseProcessor.

- Gordon


